reviews.text: Basic and simple station with 4 platforms. You can purchase tickets from machine or ticket desk and has a cafe inside the station at platforms 1 and 2. It is also very close to the mall and has a Starbucks cafe across the road.
Why do some people want to make your travel experience bad before it has even started? Enquire at ticket desk.

Please thank one of your staff - Sandra - for her help today - 5/4/19.
She helped me with my case and made sure I got the right train to Three Bridges. A very nice young lady!

Definitely a lacking station that feels old and damp in lots of places. Step free access is possible to platforms 3, 4 and 5 via lifts but not to platforms 1 and 2 which are served by stopping trains towards London. Completely unacceptable.
Friendly staffs. They should have lifts.
